From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 03:55:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Track DualSense speaker streams by sink.

Spider-Man Remastered can keep using a controller speaker stream across
DualSense disconnect/reconnect or DS <-> DS Edge switches. We were only
marking a stream for controller-speaker retargeting when it matched the strict
mono format check. That lets some streams route to the controller speaker at
startup but skip the live retarget list, so they remain bound to the removed
physical sink after the first controller switch.

Track any non-haptic stream that is actually connected to a DualSense speaker
sink. Keep the raw haptic path separate, but make controller-speaker/effect
streams sticky for hotplug retargeting regardless of the channel count the game
requested.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 7 +++----
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 99999999999..aaaaaaaaaaa 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -2951,10 +2951,9 @@ static NTSTATUS pulse_create_stream(void *args)
     else if ((resolved_device = pulse_resolve_device_name(connect_device)))
         connect_device = resolved_device;
 
-    if (!dualsense_mono_candidate && !haptic_candidate && pulse_stream_dualsense_mono_format(stream)
-            && pulse_name_is_dualsense_speaker_sink(connect_device))
+    if (!dualsense_mono_candidate && !haptic_candidate && pulse_name_is_dualsense_speaker_sink(connect_device))
     {
-        TRACE("Tracking DualSense mono stream for selected speaker sink %s.\n",
-                debugstr_a(connect_device));
+        TRACE("Tracking DualSense speaker stream for selected sink %s, channels %u.\n",
+                debugstr_a(connect_device), stream->ss.channels);
         dualsense_mono_candidate = TRUE;
     }
 
